00:20:48.120 --> 00:20:51.880
single-chain cathepsins that then, when they shouldn't, start to

358
00:20:51.900 --> 00:20:54.940
break down material within the extracellular space

359
00:20:55.000 --> 00:20:58.880
that doesn't allow for, or causes a

360
00:20:58.940 --> 00:21:02.780
failure to establish an appropriate niche for these cells to seed

361
00:21:02.860 --> 00:21:04.070
and colonize efficiently.

362
00:21:05.720 --> 00:21:09.260
And that is specific to the liver and not to the pancreas.

363
00:21:09.340 --> 00:21:12.020
We don't quite know why, but this is where we are.

